ratings.rComments: She is the worst teacher I have ever had in my life. I am an "A" student, and got a B- (for the record, I got an A in orgo 2). She sets you up to fail. Exams do not reflect the material and are so difficult that the average hovers around 30%. Our exam average was lower than usual and she blamed it on us not studying hard enough. Worst teacher ever!

Worst teacher and hardest class I have ever taken in my life. I usually get good grades and did not do well in her class. She is AWFUL. She got put on probation for giving out too many low grades - true story. Stay away at all costs.
very helpful teacher.

SHE SHOULD NOT BE TEACHING A SECOND SEMESTER COURSE OF THIS STUFF.  I HAVE HER NOW AT SIUE AND SHE SUCKS.  F*** my life.  She is so fake! Honestly who the f*** wants to be a chemist in real life any ways.... LAME!
She is now at SIU-E stay away from her. She is totally usless, you have to teach yourself, gives homework then says it will not be covered on test. I wish I could go to someone else to learn this.
I think she was pretty good. She made me understand a lot. Very good one on one, always available, and very understanding. I really liked her. I don't know why ppl hate her

The things she taught and the daily assignments she gave were incredibly easy compared to the exams.  She doesn't prepare you to succeed on her exams at all.  Her test averages are incredibly low, often in the 30's.  I got I think 30 or 40 %'s and got a B+.

I thought she had a really clear, pleasant voice--she just isn't the best teacher.  The material is there, but there's something lacking.  Thankfully they offered a video recording of the lecture, since it's usually at 8AM.  The tests are really difficult, to the point where a 13/150 or so counts as a C.

she can't teach for anything. she may be fine one on one, but with a lecture hall of 200, not everyone can see her so, basically, she's useless. i do better on the exams by teaching myself than going to class.
wonderful professor.  difficult class but fun overall and laidback. easy to talk to and contact.

She's the worst professor this university has on staff!! -Her exams reflect nothing even remotely related to the lecture notes. -She's never available to answer questions. ex) goes out of town the day before an exam and cancels office hours. -She won't respond to emails. -She sets you up to fail. Orgo would be do-able if she wasn't the professor.

Lets put it this way.I'm a straight A student who frequently gets A+'s.I got an A- in her class.The exams are EXTREMELY difficult and DO NOT reflect truly what is taught in lecture.I wanted to shoot myself in the face.I really like the subject of Orgo itself. You must put in A LOT of work, and that still may not help you. Kind of an okay teacher.

She tries to be helpful but the class is very tough and although many want to blame her teaching, I blame the difficulty of the exams. The exams she writes are very too difficult. The only way to succeed in this class is to watch lecture ON TIME!!!, go to a couple of SI's every week and read the book. If you do those three things, YOU CAN DO WELL!!
Dr. Miller is somewhat disorganized in lecture, but she is great 1 on 1 in office hours. She really loves what she does, and organic chemistry is not that bad if you work hard.

Likely the worst organic chem professor at the school. Was put on probation for extremely low test averages (spring 08 exam 2 = 26% avg, exam 3 = 37% avg). What is taught rarely reflects what will be on the exam. Attending SI sessions is one of the only ways to do well

It's a shame that Lynne Miller is the person who has to introduce so many people to organic chemistry.  The class is terrible thanks to her awful teaching.  I would do all old practice exams/ book homework/ read from the book/ and attend lecture on time.  I would study for days in advance and yet I still got a B in the class. She's AWFUL.

When I found errors on tests and labs multiple times she agreed that her answers were incorrect and said it wouldn't be fair to the other students to give me credit but not to worry she would add them at the end.  What a lie.  When the end came she was unavailable at all times.   I have formally filed a complaint with Chem department

Your grade on the exams is determined by how naturally good you are at organic chemistry. I know some ppl who study a ton and end up with a very low grade... and some ppl who just look at a mechanism and get it w/o ever listening to lectures or anything. It's easy to hate dr. miller if you are not gifted in orgo.

My worst class so far in any level of school.  Miller is an unbearable lecturer in my opinion.  Its tough to get an A when on tests an A is a 40/150 and a B is a 32/150, so a few % decide your letter grade.  With such low averages it can be a game of luck if you can figure out one more problem and get the better grade.

She was a nice professor, but as most everyone has already stated on the site, her exams were extremely hard. I compared organic exams we at UofI to some of my friends who go to good colleges( Loyola, Wisconsin,Indiana) and our exams were so much harder than their's! Maybe all chemists should just rewrite the organic chem curriculum because it suck

I thought that this class is hard. In discussion, we work as a group, and most of the time I understand the material given. Butit does not show in my exams. Every exam just depresses me to find out I am going to fail this class. I used my notes, book, but I had no time to meet the professor to get help. Studying early and old test did not help.

Lynne Miller,  if you think you are an awesome professor, there is no need to write on this website.  I think you should seriously look over these comments and try to learn from them.  I agree these comments are quite harsh.  However, we won't make these comments up if we like you and think you are an awesone professor.
An extremely hard class. If you don't read the text or attend SI office hours it will be difficult. Her exams were extremely hard, so the curves were pretty huge.

She is very nice and will teach you everything you need to know about the subject. People are pissed off because they didnt stay on top of everything and all that and thats reasonable because the online lectures are always there. I did 8 in 3 days and thats annoying so keep up do the exams and talk to her about any problems.

I'm not sure where all this is coming from! I think I am an awesome professor! Sure my exams may be so hard that God himself couldn't do them, but what's the point in having exams that mortals can complete in one and a half hours?

well it's almost over and what can i say...i'm not happy with the amount of o-chem i learned in this class. my exam average so far has been about a 50 percent and that's probably gonna be a B or a C, possibly an A if im lucky with the curve. what kind of class gives an A to someone who only knows 2/3rds of the material? i was duped this semester.

I feel as if orgo lectures were useless this year. most of my success came from self study and reading other materials. i strongly feel that very important concepts in this class are merely glossed over in the lectures and book readings you CANNOT rely on the class materials to do well. i guarantee you will fail if you do just that.

Lynne Miller is NOT a good professor.  She purposely writes exams to bring people's grades down.  Only those who naturally understand organic chemistry exceed in her class because she does little to teach it.  SI leaders deserve all credit for anyone learning anything in this class.
No Comments

Lynne Miller is a horrible professor.  Who lets this lady teach?  The University should really look into how poor of a job she's doing- any positive reviews of her on this website were probably written by her family members (or herself) because anyone whose taken a class with her knows how awful she truly is.  Take orgo with another professor.

Dr. Miller is one of the best chemistry teachers I have had. She takes hard concepts and makes them easier to understand. She is very clear and you can tell she chooses her wording very carefully. Sure, this class is a lot of work, but if you are willing to put in the effort I guarantee it will be worth it. If you are not, orgo may not be for you.

Might be the worst teacher in the history of this school.  Seems nice at first, but as the semester goes on she finds ways to make you hate her.  Lectures are terribly taught/explained and she always sounds like she is out of breath which is irritating.

I had her for 232 and 233 this summer, and I thought she was cool at first, but after this, I really don't think so.  She rarely responds to emails, and there was a wrong answer on the key for our first exam, but she refused to go back and regrade the exams! So, the people who know their stuff got it wrong and the people that don't know their stuff

Absolutely horrible. She changed the exam format in the middle of the semester without letting us know. I got a 58 out of 150 points and I was 1 point away from an A. Her lectures tell you all sorts of useless crap and don't actually teach you anything. The SI leaders should be teaching the class because I learned EVERYTHING from them.

Dishonest, Disorganized Had her kids at offices hours and would not unlock door while I waited outside. said she was having "mommy time" Worst teacher I have ever had. Needs to be fired ASAP. My younger sister is attending a different college because of horror stories regarding her.

I don't think she is bad at all. She's really clear and good at keeping you focused when she lectures at 8am. She's ALWAYS available when you need her. Take Moore and then you can complain. His exams are DIFFICULT and impossible. Her exams are difficult as well, but hey which science in this place is not?

Lynn Miller is the worst professor at the University of Illinois. To all students enrolled in her course, definitely drop it and take it with another professor! She is horribly unorganized and lied to me about my grade. She wont help you with anything and she posts final grades on the website after they've been locked in. Stay away from her...

The lab lecture was useless and the course was poorly run. Grades were never posted on time. It took her two weeks to post our final grades, and the final exam was 28 questions multiple choice AND SOME OF THE QUESTIONS WERE WORTH EIGHT POINTS because the test was out of 150.

Good lecturer but every other aspect of the lab class was a mess. Class power points always posted late, and test and lab grades always took weeks to come online. I would highly not recommend her because you will get so constantly frustrated for broken promises on her part.

At the beginning of the year she seemed very friendly and helpful. As the semester progressed she wasnt nearly as nice and she wouldnt get back to the students about questions. She isnt very well organized either. One good point was that she was very straight to the point in the lab lectures so we never had to stay for all 50minutes for lab lecture

shes the worst teacher ive ever had in college. seemed to use the fact that she was pregnant for an exuse to everything. honestly, she did not help lecturing. find some old tests and study those. went to class for one unit and it did nothing for my grade. stopped going after that and i actually improved because i knew i had 2 teach myself the stuff

In both classes she was extremly unfair and difficult! She has snuck around the system and locked the grades at U of I before displaying it on the course website so that nobody can complain! I though chemistry couldn't get any more ridiculous, but these two classes prove that she is the worst out of all my chem teachers! Also had favorites!

She tried to be helpful but instead was very disorganized. There seemed to be no communication between her and her TAs for 233, and reports took forever to be returned. 232 was not too hard, 233 was easy overall, but the final was increadibly hard and didn't test us on what we learned, but on how many picky details we were able to memorize.
Very disorganized and took forever getting things back to you. Not very accessible and cancelled office hours often. Overall, was not a good professor.

A good lecturer but is incredibly lazy as far as getting things back to students on time. MC midterm took over 3-1/2 weeks! Most labs took 2-4 weeks to get back . Didn't want to return pre-labs before post-lab was due. Took off up to 10pts on 30-35 pt labs for not doing things that weren't on the "to-do" list. Horribly disorganized!
yes this is a hard class, but miller makes it worse.  go listen to van der donk.  hes a lot better.

It is a difficult class, but if you prepare enough in advance for exams, you'll do fine.  I did not read assigned readings, went to no SI sessions, but just studied well in advance and got an A in the class. A lot of students didn't think she was a good lecturer, but I thought she was much easier to understand than Van Der Donk.
She's super hot!!!!  I could listen to her talk all day long and never be distracted.

It's a hard class. Prof. Miller is quite self-conscious, and sometimes I feel as though it hurts her from an authoritative standpoint. All I can say is, don't dick around and you should be fine in her class.

Yes, orgo and orgo tests are a pain, but if you show up to class/watch the online lectures and go over the practice problems, you should be fine. The class average on tests are usually about 50% so there is a nice curve. Go to the SI sessions for additional practice and do those really annoying online pre-lectures (the points add up in the end)
